window.__QUIZ_DATA__=[{"id":"theory>Mathematics>2017>1>a","subject":"Mathematics","year":"2017","type":"Theory","sub_label":"a","group":"FINAL","topic":"NUMBER AND NUMERATION : LOGARITHMS","question":"If (y - 1)log104 = ylog1016, without using mathematical tables or calculator, find the value of y.  (Leaving the answer in whole number)","images":[],"marking_scheme":"(y - 1)log104 = ylog1016  Divide both sides by y  y-1ylog104=log1016  Divide both sides by log104  y-1y=log1016log104  Recall:  logbalogbc=logca  log1016log104=log418  y-1y=log1016log104givesy-1y=log416  y-1y=log416  y-1y=2  y - 1 = 2y  -1 = 2y - y  -1 = y  y = -1","marks":"4","difficulty":"3"},{"id":"theory>Mathematics>2017>1>b","subject":"Mathematics","year":"2017","type":"Theory","sub_label":"b","group":"FINAL","topic":"NUMBER AND NUMERATION : RATIO, PROPORTIONS AND RATES","question":"When I walk from my house at 4Km/h, I will get to the office 30 minutes later than when I walk at 5km/h. Calculate the distance between my house and office.  (Leaving the answer in whole number)","images":[],"marking_scheme":"V1 = 4kmh-1  t1 = (x + 0.5)hr  V2 = 5kmh-1  t2 = (x)hr  D1 = D2  Recall: V=Dt  D = Vt ----------- *  D1 = D2  V1t1 = V2t2  4 \u00d7 (x + 0.5) = 5 \u00d7 (x)  4(x + 0.5) = 5x   2 = x  x = 2hours     D1 = V1t1  D1 = 4 \u00d7 (2 + 0.5)  D1 = 4(2.5) = 10km  D2 = V2t2  D2 = 5(2)  D2 = 10km  D1 = D2 = 10km","marks":"4","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"theory>Mathematics>2017>2>a","subject":"Mathematics","year":"2017","type":"Theory","sub_label":"a","group":"FINAL","topic":"ALGEBRAIC PROCESSES : LINEAR EQUATIONS IN ONE VARIABLE","question":"Solve the equation:  23(3x-5)-35(2x-3)=3     Provide your final answer as a fraction a/b","images":[],"marking_scheme":"23(3x-5)-35(2x-3)=3  (6x - 103)-(6x - 95)=3  5(6x-10)-3(6x-9)15=3  30x-50-18x+2715=3  12x - 23 = 45  12x = 45 + 23  12x = 68  x=6812=173","marks":"4","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"theory>Mathematics>2017>2>b","subject":"Mathematics","year":"2017","type":"Theory","sub_label":"b","group":"FINAL","topic":"PLANE GEOMETRY : ANGLES","question":"In the diagram, \u2220STQ = m, \u2220TUQ = 80\u00b0, \u2220UPQ = r, \u2220PQU = n and \u2220RQT = 88\u00b0.  Find the value of (m + n).  (Leaving the answer in whole number)","images":["data:image/png;base64,","data:image/png;base64,"],"marking_scheme":"Label the angle between n and 88\u00b0 as x, so that the diagram now becomes    In \u0394QPU,  80\u00b0 = r + n ( exterior \u2220 of a triangle = the sum of two opposite interior \u2220s)  In \u0394QUT  m = 80 + x ( same reason as above)  n + x + 88\u00b0 = 180\u00b0 (sum of angles on a straight line)  Now, let us look at the three equations that we have:  r + n = 80 --------------- (1)  80 + x = m -------------- (2)  n + x + 88\u00b0 = 180\u00b0 ----------------- (3)  From (2), x = m - 80  substitute for x = m - 80 in (3)  n + (m - 80) + 88 = 180\u00b0  n + m - 80 + 88 = 180\u00b0  n + m = 172\u00b0","marks":"4","difficulty":"1"},{"id":"theory>Mathematics>2017>3>a","subject":"Mathematics","year":"2017","type":"Theory","sub_label":"a","group":"FINAL","topic":"TRIGONOMETRY : ANGLES OF ELEVATION AND DEPRESSION","question":"The angle of depresion of a point P on the ground from the top T of a building is 23.6\u00b0. If the distance from P to the foot of the building is 50m, calculate, correct to the nearest metre, the height of the building.  (Leaving the answer in whole number)","images":["data:image/png;base64,"],"marking_scheme":"tan 23.6 = h/50m  h = 50m \u00d7 tan 23.6\u00b0  h = 21.8m \u2248 22.0m to the nearest metre.","marks":"4","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"theory>Mathematics>2017>3>b","subject":"Mathematics","year":"2017","type":"Theory","sub_label":"b","group":"FINAL","topic":"PLANE GEOMETRY : TRIANGLES AND POLYGONS","question":"In the diagram, P//SU, QS//TR, /SR/ = 6cm and /RU/ = 10cm. If the area of \u0394TRU = 45cm2, calculate the area of trapezium QTUS.  (Leaving the answer in whole number)","images":["data:image/png;base64,","data:image/png;base64,"],"marking_scheme":"N.B: /QT/ = /SR/ = 6cm (opposite sides of 11grm)  Now, re-draw the diagram as:    N.B: The height h of \u0394TRU = The height of trapezium QTUS  45cm2=12\u00d710\u00d7h  (From A = 1/2 bh)  h = 9cm   Recall:  Area of Trapezium = 1/2 (sum of parallel sides) \u00d7 height  AreaofTrapeziumQTUS=12(6+16)9  = 1/2 (22)9 = 99cm2","marks":"4","difficulty":"3"},{"id":"theory>Mathematics>2017>4>a","subject":"Mathematics","year":"2017","type":"Theory","sub_label":"a","group":"FINAL","topic":"NUMBER AND NUMERATION : SEQUENCE AND SERIES","question":"If the sixth term of an Arithmetic Progression (A.P.) is 37 and the sum of the first six terms is 147, find the first term  (Leaving the answer in whole number)","images":[],"marking_scheme":"T6 = 37  S6 = 147  Recall: Tn = a + (n - 1)d ----------- *  Sn=n2(a+Tn)-------------**  T6 = a + 5d = 37  S6 = 3(a + 37) = 147  a + 5d = 37 ------------- (1)  3a + 111 = 147 ---------- (2)  Divide (2) through by 3  a + 37 + 49 ------------- (3)  combine (1) and (3)  a + 5d = 37 ---------- (1)  a + 37 = 49 ------------ (3)  from (3), a = 12  substitute for a = 12 in (1)  12 + 5d = 37  5d = 25  d = 5    - First term  T1 = a = 12","marks":"4","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"theory>Mathematics>2017>4>b","subject":"Mathematics","year":"2017","type":"Theory","sub_label":"b","group":"FINAL","topic":"NUMBER AND NUMERATION : SEQUENCE AND SERIES","question":"If the sixth term of an Arithmetic Progression (A.P.) is 37 and the sum of the first six terms is 147, find the sum of the first fifteen terms.  (Leaving the answer in whole number)","images":[],"marking_scheme":"Sum of first fifteen terms   S15=152(a+T15)  T15 = a + 14d = 12 + 14(5) = 82  S15=152(12+82)  =152(94)= 15(47) = 705","marks":"1","difficulty":"3"},{"id":"theory>Mathematics>2017>5>a","subject":"Mathematics","year":"2017","type":"Theory","sub_label":"a","group":"","topic":"STATISTICS AND PROBABILITY. : STATISTICS","question":"Out of 120 customers in a shop, 45 bought both bags, and shoes. If all the customers bought either bags or shoes and 11 more customers bought shoes than bags; illustrate this information in a diagram.","images":["data:image/png;base64,"],"marking_scheme":"Before we put anything in the diagram above, let us analyse the information given in the question.  U = 120  (S \u222a B) = U = 120  (S \u222a B)c = \u2205  S \u2229 B = 45  S = So + S \u2229 B --------------- (1)  B = Bo + S \u2229 B ------------ (2)  S = B + 11 ------------------ (3)  S = So + 45 ----------------(1)  B = Bo + 45 ---------------- (2)  S = B + 11 ------------------------ (3)  substitute for (3) in (1)  B + 11 = So + 45  So = B - 34  Bo = B - 45 {from (2)}","marks":"4","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"theory>Mathematics>2017>5>b","subject":"Mathematics","year":"2017","type":"Theory","sub_label":"b","group":"FINAL","topic":"STATISTICS AND PROBABILITY. : STATISTICS","question":"Out of 120 customers in a shop, 45 bought both bags, and shoes. If all the customers bought either bags or shoes and 11 more customers bought shoes than bags, find the number of customers who bought shoes.  (Leaving the answer in whole number)","images":[],"marking_scheme":"To find the number of customers who bought shoes.  From what we have in the diagram,  U = (S \u222a B) = S + B - (S \u2229 B)  120 = (B - 34) + (45) + (B - 45)  120 = B - 34 + B  154 = 2B  B = 77  S = B + 11 = 77 + 11 = 88  88 customers bought shoes.","marks":"4","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"theory>Mathematics>2017>5>c","subject":"Mathematics","year":"2017","type":"Theory","sub_label":"c","group":"FINAL","topic":"STATISTICS AND PROBABILITY. : PROBABILITY","question":"Out of 120 customers in a shop, 45 bought both bags, and shoes. If all the customers bought either bags or shoes and 11 more customers bought shoes than bags, calculate the probability that a customer selected at random bought bags.     Provide your final answer as a fraction a/b","images":[],"marking_scheme":"Probability that a customer selected at random bought bags.  P(bags)=Number of customers who bought bagsTotal number of customers    =77120","marks":"4","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"theory>Mathematics>2017>6>a","subject":"Mathematics","year":"2017","type":"Theory","sub_label":"a","group":"FINAL","topic":"NUMBER AND NUMERATION : FINANCIAL ARITHMETIC","question":"A manufacturing company requires 3 hours of direct labour to process every \u20a687.00 worth of raw materials. If the company uses \u20a630,450.00 worth of raw materials, what amount should it budget for direct labour at \u20a618,25 per hour?  (Leaving the answer in two decimal places)","images":[],"marking_scheme":"\u20a687.00 worth of raw material requires 3 hours.  Let us calculate the time taken to process \u20a630,450.00 worth of raw materials  \u20a687.00 \u2192 3 hour  \u20a630,450.00 \u2192 x  8730,450=3x  2930,450=1x  29x = 30,450  x=30,45029  x = 1050 hours  It is given in the question that 1 hour will cost \u20a618.25, now let us. Calculate how much 1050 hours will cost.  1 hour = \u20a618.25  1050 hours = x  11050=18.25x  x = 1050(18.25)  x = \u20a619,162.50K","marks":"4","difficulty":"3"},{"id":"theory>Mathematics>2017>6>b>i","subject":"Mathematics","year":"2017","type":"Theory","sub_label":"i","group":"","topic":"NUMBER AND NUMERATION : SIMPLE INTEREST AND COMPOUND INTEREST","question":"An investor invested \u20a6x in bank M at the rate of 6% simple interest per annum. If a total of \u20a68,000,000.00 was invested in two banks and the investor received a total of \u20a62,320,000.00 as interest from two banks after 4 years, calculate the values of x and y","images":[],"marking_scheme":"Let us analyse the two banks separately  Bank M  Principal, Pm = \u20a6x  Rate, Rm = 6%  Bank N  Principal, Pn = \u20a6y  Rate, Rn = 8%  The amount received in both banks as interests  Im + In = \u20a62,320,000.00  The total invested in both banks   Pm + Pn = \u20a68,000,000.00  Time, T = 4 years  Now let us calculate:  Recall:   S.I=PRT100  Let Pm and Pn be a and b respectively.  Im=a\u00d76\u00d74100  Im = 0.24a ------- (1)  In=b\u00d78\u00d74100  In = 0.32b ------------- (2)  0.24a + 0.32b = 2,320,000 -------------- (3)  a + b = 8,000,000 -------------- (4)  From (4), b = 8,000,000 - a ----------- (5)  substitute for (5) in (3)  0.24a + 0.32(8,000,000 - a) = 2,320,000  -0.08a = \u20a6(2,320,000 - 2,560,000)  -0.08a = -\u20a6240,000  a = \u20a63,000,000  b = \u20a68,000,000 - \u20a63,000,000= \u20a65,000,000.    To calculate the values of x and y  x = Pm = a = \u20a63,000,000  y = Pn = b = \u20a65,000,000","marks":"4","difficulty":"3"},{"id":"theory>Mathematics>2017>6>b>ii","subject":"Mathematics","year":"2017","type":"Theory","sub_label":"ii","group":"FINAL","topic":"NUMBER AND NUMERATION : SIMPLE INTEREST AND COMPOUND INTEREST","question":"An investor invested \u20a6x in bank M at the rate of 6% simple interest per annum. If a total of \u20a68,000,000.00 was invested in two banks and the investor received a total of \u20a62,320,000.00 as interest from two banks after 4 years, calculate the interest paid by the second bank.  (Leaving the answer in whole number)","images":[],"marking_scheme":"Interest paid by the second bank, N  In=Pn\u00d7Rn\u00d7Tn100  In=5,000,000\u00d78\u00d74100  In = \u20a61,600,000","marks":"4","difficulty":"3"},{"id":"theory>Mathematics>2017>7>a","subject":"Mathematics","year":"2017","type":"Theory","sub_label":"a","group":"","topic":"ALGEBRAIC PROCESSES : FORMULATION AND EVALUATION OF ALGEBRAIC PROCESSES","question":"Copy and complete the table of values for the equation: y = 2x2 - 7x - 9 for -3 \u2264 x \u2264 6.  x-3-2-10123456y139-14-126","images":[],"marking_scheme":"x-3-2-10123456y139-14-126  We are given that:  y = 2x2 - 7x - 9  When x = -3  y = 2(-3)2 - 7(-3) - 9  = 2(9) + 21 - 9  = 18 + 21 - 9  = 30   When x = -1  y = 2(-1)2 - 7(-1) - 9  = 2(1) + 7 - 9  = 0    When x = 2  y = 2(2)2 - 7(2) - 9  = 2(4) - 14 - 9  = 8 - 23   = -15  when x = 4  y = 2(4)2 - 7(4) - 9  = 2(16) - 28 - 9  = 32 - 37  = -5  When x = 6  y = 2(6)2 - 7(6) - 9   = 2(36) - 42 - 9  = 21  v = 8 - 23   = -15  when x = 4  y = 2(6)2 - 7(6) - 9   = 72 - 51   = 21  Now, the complete table  x-3-2-10123456y30130-9-14-15-12-5621","marks":"4","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"theory>Mathematics>2017>7>b","subject":"Mathematics","year":"2017","type":"Theory","sub_label":"b","group":"","topic":"ALGEBRAIC PROCESSES : GRAPHS OF LINEAR AND QUADRATIC FUNCTIONS","question":"Using scales of 2cm to 1 unit on the x-axis and 2cm to 4 units on the y-axis, draw the graph of y = 2x2 - 7x - 9 for -3 \u2264 x \u2264 6.","images":["data:image/png;base64,"],"marking_scheme":"","marks":"4","difficulty":"3"},{"id":"theory>Mathematics>2017>7>c>i","subject":"Mathematics","year":"2017","type":"Theory","sub_label":"i","group":"","topic":"ALGEBRAIC PROCESSES : GRAPHS OF LINEAR AND QUADRATIC FUNCTIONS","question":"Use the graph to estimate the roots of equation 2x2 - 7x = 26","images":[],"marking_scheme":"-1 and 4.5","marks":"4","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"theory>Mathematics>2017>7>c>ii","subject":"Mathematics","year":"2017","type":"Theory","sub_label":"ii","group":"","topic":"ALGEBRAIC PROCESSES : GRAPHS OF LINEAR AND QUADRATIC FUNCTIONS","question":"Use the graph to estimate the coordinates of the minimum point of y.","images":[],"marking_scheme":"(1.5, -12.7)","marks":"4","difficulty":"1"},{"id":"theory>Mathematics>2017>7>c>iii","subject":"Mathematics","year":"2017","type":"Theory","sub_label":"iii","group":"","topic":"ALGEBRAIC PROCESSES : LINEAR INEQUALITIES","question":"Use the graph to estimate the range of values for which 2x2 - 7x","images":[],"marking_scheme":"(x + 1)(x - 9/2)","marks":"4","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"theory>Mathematics>2017>8>a","subject":"Mathematics","year":"2017","type":"Theory","sub_label":"a","group":"FINAL","topic":"STATISTICS AND PROBABILITY. : STATISTICS","question":"Marks12345Number of studentsm + 2 m - 1 2m - 3 m + 5 3m - 4  The table shows the distribution of marks scored by some students in a test.  Ifthemeanmarkis3623,findthevalueofm.  (Leaving the answer in whole number)","images":[],"marking_scheme":"Recall:  Mean=\u2211fx\u2211f  7523=1(m+2)+2(m-1)+3(2m-3)+4(m+5)+5(3m-4)(m+2)+(m-1)+(2m-3)+(m+5)+(3m-4)  7523=28m-98m-1  75(8m - 1) = 23(28m - 9)  44m = 132  m = 3","marks":"4","difficulty":"3"},{"id":"theory>Mathematics>2017>8>b>i","subject":"Mathematics","year":"2017","type":"Theory","sub_label":"i","group":"FINAL","topic":"STATISTICS AND PROBABILITY. : STATISTICS","question":"Find the interquartile range  (Leaving the answer in whole number)","images":[],"marking_scheme":"To calculate the inter-quartile range   = Q3 - Q1  xfc.f155227331048185523  Q3=34\u00d723=17.25  Q1=14\u00d723=5.75  Q3 - Q1 = 4 - 2 = 2 marks","marks":"4","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"theory>Mathematics>2017>8>b>ii","subject":"Mathematics","year":"2017","type":"Theory","sub_label":"ii","group":"FINAL","topic":"STATISTICS AND PROBABILITY. : PROBABILITY","question":"Find the probability of selecting a student who scored at least 4 marks in the test.     Provide your final answer as a fraction a/b","images":[],"marking_scheme":"Probability of selecting a student who scored at least 4 marks in the test.  * The number of students who scored at least 4 marks = 13  * The total number of students = 23  P(at least 4 marks) = 13/23","marks":"4","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"theory>Mathematics>2017>9>a>i","subject":"Mathematics","year":"2017","type":"Theory","sub_label":"i","group":"","topic":"PLANE GEOMETRY : CIRCLES","question":"PQ is a tangent to a circle RsT at the point S. PRT is a straight line, \u2220TPS = 34\u00b0 and \u2220TSQ = 65\u00b0.  Illustrate the information in a diagram.","images":["data:image/png;base64,"],"marking_scheme":"","marks":"4","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"theory>Mathematics>2017>9>a>ii","subject":"Mathematics","year":"2017","type":"Theory","sub_label":"ii","group":"","topic":"PLANE GEOMETRY : ANGLES","question":"Find the value of   \u2220RTS  \u2220SRP","images":[],"marking_scheme":"N.B: \u2220TSQ = \u2220TRS = 65\u00b0 (angle in alternate segment)  \u2220PRS + \u2220TRS = 180\u00b0 (Angle on a straight line)  \u2220PRS + 65\u00b0 = 180\u00b0  \u2220PRS = 115\u00b0  In \u0394PRS  \u2220PRS + \u2220RPS + \u2220PSR = 180\u00b0 (sum of *angles* in a triangle)  115\u00b0 + 34\u00b0 + \u2220PSR = 180\u00b0  149\u00b0 + \u2220PSR = 180\u00b0  \u2220PSR = 31\u00b0  \u2220PSR + \u2220TSQ + \u2220TSR = 180\u00b0 (sum of angles on a straight line)  31\u00b0 + 65\u00b0 + \u2220TSR = 180\u00b0  96\u00b0 + \u2220TSR = 180\u00b0  \u2220TSR = 84\u00b0  In \u0394RST  \u2220RST + \u2220RTS + \u2220TRS = 180\u00b0 (sum of *angles* in a Delta*)  84\u00b0 + \u2220RTS + 65\u00b0 = 180\u00b0  149\u00b0 + \u2220RTS = 180\u00b0  \u2220RTS = 31\u00b0  A. \u2220RTS = 31\u00b0  B. \u2220SRP = 115\u00b0","marks":"4","difficulty":"1"},{"id":"theory>Mathematics>2017>9>b","subject":"Mathematics","year":"2017","type":"Theory","sub_label":"b","group":"FINAL","topic":"PLANE GEOMETRY : ANGLES","question":"In the diagram, /VZ/ = /YZ/, \u2220YXZ = 20 and \u2220ZVY = 52\u00b0.  Calculate the size of \u2220WYZ","images":["data:image/png;base64,"],"marking_scheme":"\u2220XV + 52\u00b0 = 180\u00b0 (sum of angles on a straight line)  \u2220XVZ = 180\u00b0 - 52\u00b0  \u2220XZY = 180\u00b0 - (20\u00b0 + 128\u00b0)  = 32\u00b0  \u2220WYZ + 32 = 52\u00b0  \u2220WYZ = 20\u00b0","marks":"4","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"theory>Mathematics>2017>10>a","subject":"Mathematics","year":"2017","type":"Theory","sub_label":"a","group":"FINAL","topic":"TRIGONOMETRY : SINE, COSINE AND TANGENT OF AN ANGLE","question":"Given that sin x = 5/13 , 0\u00b0 findcosx-2sinx2tanx     Provide your final answer as a fraction = a/b","images":["data:image/png;base64,"],"marking_scheme":"Sinx=513--------------*  0\u00b0  N.B: sinx=opphyp    cosx=1213,tanx=512  cosx - 2sinx2tanx=12/13 - 2(5/13)2(5/12)  =12/13 - 10/135/6=213\u00f756  =213\u00d765=1265","marks":"4","difficulty":"3"},{"id":"theory>Mathematics>2017>10>b>i","subject":"Mathematics","year":"2017","type":"Theory","sub_label":"i","group":"FINAL","topic":"TRIGONOMETRY : ANGLES OF ELEVATION AND DEPRESSION","question":"A ladder, LA, leans against a vertical pole at a point L which is 9.6 metres above the ground. Another ladder, LB, 12 metres long, leans on the opposite side of the pole and at the same straight line as the foot of the pole, calculate, correct to 2 significant figures, the length of ladder LA  (Leaving the answer in whole number)","images":["data:image/png;base64,","data:image/png;base64,"],"marking_scheme":"Diagrammatically, the information can be represented as:    Length of ladder LA  Let the length of LA be y m  In \u0394L \u00d7 B  (9.6)2 + (XB)2 = (12)2  (XB)2 = (12)2 - (9.6)2  (XB)2 = 144 - 92.16  (XB)2 = 51.84  XB = &radic;51.84&nbsp;  XB = 7.2m  N.B: 10m = AX + XB  AX = 10m - XB  XB = 7.2m  XB = 7.2m  /AX/ = 10m - 7.2m  = 2.8m    y2 = (2.8)2 + (9.6)2  y2 = 7.84 + 92.16  y2 = 100  y = &radic;100&nbsp; = 10m","marks":"4","difficulty":"3"},{"id":"theory>Mathematics>2017>10>b>ii","subject":"Mathematics","year":"2017","type":"Theory","sub_label":"ii","group":"FINAL","topic":"TRIGONOMETRY : ANGLES OF ELEVATION AND DEPRESSION","question":"A ladder, LA, leans against a vertical pole at a point L which is 9.6 metres above the ground. Another ladder, LB, 12 metres long, leans on the opposite side of the pole and at the same straight line as the foot of the pole, calculate, correct to 2 significant figures, the angle which LA makes with the ground.     Provide your final answer in one decimal place= ab.0","images":["data:image/png;base64,"],"marking_scheme":"Angle which LA makes with the ground    Sin\u03b8 = 9.6/10  \u03b8 = sin-1(0.96)  \u03b8 = 73.7\u00b0","marks":"4","difficulty":"3"},{"id":"theory>Mathematics>2017>11>a","subject":"Mathematics","year":"2017","type":"Theory","sub_label":"a","group":"FINAL","topic":"NUMBER AND NUMERATION : RATIO, PROPORTIONS AND RATES","question":"It takes 8 students two-thirds of an hour to fill 12 tanks with water. How many tanks of water will 4 students fill in one-third of an hour at the same rate?  (Leaving the answer in whole number)","images":[],"marking_scheme":"NOTE: The number of people needed to do a piece of work is inversely proportional to the time taken.  That is: N \u03b1 1/T  ALSO NOTE THAT: The higher the number of people employed to do a piece of work, the higher the fraction of the work that is completed and vice versa.  That is, N \u03b1 W  N\u03b1WT  N1T1W1=N2T2W2  In this case,  N = Number of students   T = Time taken  W = Number of water tanks   8 \u00d7 2/3  12=4 \u00d7 1/3W2  16/312=4/3W2  163\u00d7112=43\u00d71W2  1612=4W2  43=4W2  W2 = 3 tanks of water.","marks":"4","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"theory>Mathematics>2017>11>b>i","subject":"Mathematics","year":"2017","type":"Theory","sub_label":"i","group":"FINAL","topic":"PLANE GEOMETRY : CIRCLES","question":"A chord, 20cm long, is 12cm from the centre of circle. Calculate, correct to one decimal place, the angle subtended by the chord at the centre of the circle.  [Take \u03c0 = 3.142]  (Leaving the answer in two decimal places ab.c)","images":["data:image/png;base64,"],"marking_scheme":"The angle subtended by the chord   AB = 2\u03b8  In \u0394OXB,  tan\u03b8=1012=56  \u03b8=tan-1(56)  \u03b8 = 39.8\u00b0  2\u03b8 = 2(39.8\u00b0) = 79.6\u00b0","marks":"4","difficulty":"3"},{"id":"theory>Mathematics>2017>11>b>ii","subject":"Mathematics","year":"2017","type":"Theory","sub_label":"ii","group":"FINAL","topic":"PLANE GEOMETRY : CIRCLES","question":"A chord, 20cm long, is 12cm from the centre of circle. Calculate, correct to one decimal place, the perimeter of minor segment cut off by the chord.  [Take \u03c0 = 3.142]  (Leaving the answer in whole number)","images":["data:image/png;base64,"],"marking_scheme":"Perimeter of minor segment cut off by the chord.  N.B: Perimeter of the minor segment  = Length of chord + Length of arc AB  =20m+79.6360\u00d72\u00d7227\u00d7r  r can be gotten from \u0394OXB using pythagoras theorem    r2 = 122 + 102  r2 = 144 + 100  r2 = 244  r = &radic;244&nbsp; = 15.6m    Perimeter of minor segment  =20m+79.6360\u00d7447\u00d715.6  = 20m + 21.86m  = 41.68m \u2248 42.00m","marks":"4","difficulty":"3"},{"id":"theory>Mathematics>2017>12>a","subject":"Mathematics","year":"2017","type":"Theory","sub_label":"a","group":"","topic":"ALGEBRAIC PROCESSES : QUADRATIC EQUATIONS","question":"Using completing the square method, solve, correct to 2 decimal places, the equation 3y2 - 5y + 2 = 0","images":[],"marking_scheme":"3y2 - 5y + 2 = 0  Divide through by 3  y2-53y+23=0  y2-53y=-23  Add to both sides the square of half of the co-efficient of y  y2-53y+2536=-23+2536  (y-56)2=-24+2536  (y-56)2=(136)  Take the square roots of both side.  y-56=\u00b116  y=56\u00b116  y=56\u00b116  y=56+16ory=56-16  y=66ory=46  y = 1 or 2/3","marks":"4","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"theory>Mathematics>2017>12>b","subject":"Mathematics","year":"2017","type":"Theory","sub_label":"b","group":"","topic":"NUMBER AND NUMERATION : MATRICES AND DETERMINANTS","question":"M=1243,N=mxnyandMN=2134  Find the matrix N","images":[],"marking_scheme":"M=1243,N=mxnyandMN=2134  2134=1243\u00d7mxny  2134=m+nx+2y4m+3n4x+3y  m + 2n = 2 ---------- (1)  4m + 3n = 3 ----------- (2)  x + 2y = 1 ---------- (3)  4x + 3y = 4 ------------ (4)  Combine (1) and (2) to get m and n  m + 2n = 2 ------------ (1)  4m + 3n = 3 ----------- (2)  from (1) m = 2 - 2n  substitute for m = 2 - 2n in (2)  4(2 - 2n) + 3n = 3  8 - 8n + 3n = 3  -5n = -5  n = 1  substitute for n = 1 in (1)  m + 2(1) = 2  m = 2 - 2 = 0  combine (3) and (4) to get x  x + 2y = 1 --------- (3)  4x + 3y = 4 -------- (4)  From (1), x = 1 - 2y  substract for x = 1 - 2y in (4)  4(1 - 2y) + 3y = 4  4 - 8y + 3y = 4  4 - 5y = 4  -5y = 0  y = 0  substitute for y = 0 in (3)  x + 2(0) = 1  x = 1  N=0110","marks":"4","difficulty":"3"},{"id":"theory>Mathematics>2017>13>a>i","subject":"Mathematics","year":"2017","type":"Theory","sub_label":"i","group":"FINAL","topic":"ALGEBRAIC PROCESSES : BINARY OPERATIONS","question":"The operation (*) is defined on the set of real numbers, R, by x(*)y = x+y/2 , x, y \u2208R.  Evaluate3(*)25     Provide your final answer as a fraction: y=a/b","images":[],"marking_scheme":"x(*)y=x+y2  3 (*) 2/5  3 + 2/52=172\u00f72=1710","marks":"4","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"theory>Mathematics>2017>13>a>ii","subject":"Mathematics","year":"2017","type":"Theory","sub_label":"ii","group":"FINAL","topic":"ALGEBRAIC PROCESSES : BINARY OPERATIONS","question":"The operation (*) is defined on the set of real numbers, R, by x(*)y = x+y/2 , x, y   If8(*)y=814,findthevalueofy.     Provide your final answer as a fraction: y=a/b","images":[],"marking_scheme":"8 (*) y = 8 1/4  =8+y2=814  8+y2=334  4(8 + y) = 66  32 + 4y = 66  4y = 34  y=172","marks":"4","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"theory>Mathematics>2017>13>b","subject":"Mathematics","year":"2017","type":"Theory","sub_label":"b","group":"","topic":"VECTORS AND TRANSFORMATION : VECTORS IN A PLANE","question":"In\u0394ABC,AB\u0305=-46andAC=3-8,ifPisthemidpointof\u2192AB\u2192,express\u2192CP\u2192asacolumn","images":["data:image/png;base64,","data:image/png;base64,"],"marking_scheme":"\u2192CP\u2192 + \u2192AC\u2192 = \u2192AP\u2192  \u2192CP\u2192  =  \u2192AP\u2192 - \u2192AC\u2192   \u2192CP\u2192=(-23)-(3-8)  \u2192CP\u2192=-511","marks":"4","difficulty":"3"}];